  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given a `sprk_event` configId, when `<DataGrid />` mounts in Storybook, then it renders selection-mode multi-select, sortable columns, resizable columns, focus-mode keyboard nav — all from Fluent v9 native props.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `configId="nonexistent"`, when DataGrid renders, then it falls through to metadata + layoutXml defaults without throwing.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given a 1000-record entity, when user scrolls to bottom, then page 2 loads via FetchXML paging cookie within 1 second.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given user selects 5 rows on page 1 then scrolls to page 3, when checked, then all 5 selections persist.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `grep -E 'useId|useSyncExternalStore|createRoot' src/components/DataGrid/`, when run, then zero matches (React-16-safe).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="DataGrid renders with valid configId">
      <url>http://localhost:6006/?path=/story/datagrid--default-sprk-event</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Navigate to Storybook DataGrid default story</step>
        <step>Verify table renders with column headers from layoutXml</step>
        <step>Verify rows render with sample data</step>
        <step>Check console for errors</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Table visible, no console errors, columns match layoutXml</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Dark mode compliance (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle Storybook dark mode via toolbar</step>
        <step>Verify all colors adapt — no white background in dark mode</step>
        <step>Verify popover-bearing surfaces (column header menu) render correctly in dark</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>All colors via tokens.*; applyStylesToPortals working; dark mode visually correct</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Selection persists across lazy-load pages">
      <steps>
        <step>Open "Lazy load (1000 records)" story</step>
        <step>Select 5 rows on page 1</step>
        <step>Scroll to bottom — verify page 2, 3 load</step>
        <step>Scroll back to top — verify all 5 selections still checked</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Selection Set&lt;string&gt; preserved across page boundaries</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    This is the largest Phase A task and the most architecturally consequential. Three watch-outs: (1) the three-tier config resolution must be a pure function that's easy to unit-test independently — don't bake it into the component; (2) `IntersectionObserver` cleanup on unmount is mandatory or you'll leak observers across hot reloads; (3) the `useDataGridContext()` hook is what every host extension uses — get the return shape right per FR-DG-15. Parallels task 002.
  </notes>

